    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_4397988050" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4397988050" />
    <a title="~Jo~" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/28323108-jo"><img alt="~Jo~" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1643925119p2/28323108.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4397988050?book_show_action=true">Jan 30, 2022</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="~Jo~" class="user" itemprop="url" name="~Jo~" href="/user/show/28323108-jo">~Jo~</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780241277027" href="/book/show/29607501-alone-in-berlin">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/28323108-jo?shelf=to-throw-from-a-high-building">to-throw-from-a-high-building</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4397988050" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15844859852650913010">This book appears to be quite popular, here on Goodreads, and I have read some glittering reviews, with the majority of people gushing about how much they loved it. I however, most certainly did not love this, it was terrible, which is a tremendous shame, as I honestly think that with the right author, this story might have succeeded, even into something at least half readable. <br/><br/>I think the only redeemable aspect of this book is that it tells the truth, in all of it&apos;s hideous and atrocious form, </span>
  <span id="freeText15844859852650913010" style="display:none">This book appears to be quite popular, here on Goodreads, and I have read some glittering reviews, with the majority of people gushing about how much they loved it. I however, most certainly did not love this, it was terrible, which is a tremendous shame, as I honestly think that with the right author, this story might have succeeded, even into something at least half readable. <br /><br />I think the only redeemable aspect of this book is that it tells the truth, in all of it's hideous and atrocious form, and that is probably what makes this more difficult to rate so low, because this is someone's life experience. But, despite the biographical elements, it does not keep it safe from my critical eye. <br /><br />It makes me think, was the issue with the translation? What was the abundance of exclamation marks about every couple of sentences? What was with the sexist drawl?<br /><br />I'll start by stating that conversations had between characters were dreary and the characters themselves seemed not to have any appealing attributes. They kind of just accepted everything that happened, and not even with a stiff upper lip. They were flat, and they sucked the life out of me. <br /><br />The repetition was ridiculous. Everything was laid out on a plain plate, so the reader already knew what was about to happen before it happened. There was a lack of wonder or intrigue, which left me less inclined to turn the pages, but somehow I did, and I still feel nothing. <br /><br />The writing style was dreadfully unappealing and bland, and it felt like a total rush-job in parts. I failed to become engaged in the story at any point, and on one occasion, I fell into a terrific slumber. That says it all really.</span>
  <a data-text-id="15844859852650913010" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


